Currently regular transaction scripts are not allowed on Diem. This enforces the same rule in diem transactional tests, so that they mimic the real world use cases more closely. This also adds support for admin scripts.

Now if you try to send a regular transaction script:
```
//# run --signers 0x4777eb94491650dd3f095ce6f778acb6
//#     --private-key 56a26140eb233750cd14fb168c3eb4bd0782b099cde626ec8aff7f3cceb6364f
script {
    fun main() {}
}
```
The test harness will panic:
```
thread 'run_test::diem_test_harness/example.move' panicked at 'Transactions scripts are not currently allowed on Diem. If you intend to run an admin script, add the `--admin-script` option to the run command.'
```

Admin scripts do not require a private key -- they are signed using the (test) genesis key pair. 
```
//# run --signers 0xA550C18
//#     --admin-script

script {
    use DiemFramework::DiemAccount::create_validator_account;

    fun main(dr: signer, _s: signer) {
        create_validator_account(&dr, @A, x"f75daa73fc071f93593335eb9033da80", x"40");
    }
}
```
If you do provide a private key however, the admin script transaction will be signed using that key instead. Although this will likely result in the transaction being rejected:
```
Error: Transaction discarded. VMStatus: status INVALID_AUTH_KEY of type Validation
```
